			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">In 1997, after twenty years of writing novels, short stories, comics, and screenplays, Marc Laidlaw ventured into fulltime game design as a member of Valve Software.  The first game he worked on was Half-Life; the second was Half-Life 2, for which he received the Game Developers’ Choice Award for Writing.  His novels include The 37th Mandala (winner of the 1996 International Horror Guild Award for Best Novel), Dad’s Nuke, Neon Lotus, Kalifornia, and The Orchid Eater.
